Key Match Events: Marcel Sabitzer scored a winning goal for Austria with a spectacular angled finish 10 minutes from time.
Donyell Malen scored an own goal for Austria, opening the scoring.
Memphis Depay equalized for the Netherlands with a header after VAR reviewed a potential handball.
Post-Match Reflections: Ralf Rangnick's players showed great energy and kept coming despite the tough match against the Netherlands.
Austria will face the runners-up from Group F, likely Turkey or Czech Republic, in the next round, which could be considered a home game due to the Red Bull connection.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Konrad Laimer was rested due to the need to hold back in challenges.
Christoph Baumgartner came on as a substitute and made a significant impact, helping Austria win the match.
